Re-verify item ${ITEM} against the updated lighthouse + nimbus pins.

The item was rechecked recently against the current schema and Glamsterdam
target. The format and version strings are already current. What changed:

* `vendor/lighthouse` was re-pinned from `stable` (v8.1.3, March 2026) to
  `unstable` HEAD (1a6863118 "Gloas payload cache", 2026-05-13). The
  stable pin was missing months of EIP-7732 / Gloas implementation work
  that lives on `unstable`.
* `vendor/nimbus` was re-pinned from `stable` (v26.3.1) to `unstable` HEAD
  (3802d96291, 2026-05-13).

The other four clients (prysm, teku, lodestar, grandine) were already on
their active development branches and are unchanged.

This item likely contains claims of the form "lighthouse has not
implemented Gloas X" or "nimbus stale OR-fold at Gloas". Those claims
were correct against the stale `stable` pins but may now be false
positives against `unstable`. Re-verify them.

Concretely:

1. For every lighthouse claim ("X missing", "Y not wired", etc.) in the
   item body, `grep` the lighthouse tree at the new pin and confirm
   whether the surface is present or still absent. If present, the claim
   is a false positive — update the body to reflect what's there now.
2. Same for every nimbus claim — but the nimbus stale OR-folds at
   `vendor/nimbus/beacon_chain/spec/beaconstate.nim:60-67` and `:1588-1607`
   were verified to STILL BE PRESENT on `unstable`. If this item depends
   on those, the claim still holds.
3. If lighthouse + nimbus claims both vacate and they were the only
   sources of divergence, flip `impact` to `none` and remove `splits` +
   `# main_md_summary` from the front matter (per the schema rules in
   `driver/item_presubmit.sh`).
4. If splits change (e.g. `[prysm, lighthouse, teku, nimbus, grandine]`
   becomes `[prysm, teku, nimbus, grandine]` because lighthouse no longer
   diverges), update the `splits:` line and adjust the body N-vs-M
   counts.
5. If the item is a meta-audit referencing other items' claims (e.g.
   item #28), update the cross-references to match the new findings.

Other notes:

* `last_update:` → today's date.
* The Hypotheses / Findings / Cross-reference table H2 headings already
  exist; refresh content under them rather than rewriting the structure.
* `bash driver/item_presubmit.sh items/${ITEM}` must pass before commit.
* `git commit` when done with a message that calls out which claims
  vacated and which stood. The user already knows the broader context
  (re-pin + sweep), so the per-item commit message can be terse.
